<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910115-0085</DOCNO><DOCID>910115-0085.</DOCID><HL>   Canada to Offer 4 Bond Issues</HL><DATE>01/15/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   CANDA</CO><IN>BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)</IN><LP>   OTTAWA -- The Canadian government said it will offer 1.3billion Canadian dollars (US$1.13 billion) of bonds in fourissues this week.   Its sale will include 10.25% bonds, due Feb. 1, 1994;10.25% bonds, due March 1, 1996; 10.5% bonds, due March 1,2001; and 10.5% bonds, due March 15, 2021. The offering termsare to be announced today.</LP><TEXT>   The Bank of Canada has agreed to purchase at least C$100million of the new bonds. The remainder will be available topublic investors.   Proceeds of the sale will be used to redeem C$719 millionof government bonds maturing Feb. 1 and for generalgovernment purposes.</TEXT></DOC>